    • Field Detail

      • SKIP_HOT_SWAP_KEY

        public static final Key<java.lang.Boolean> SKIP_HOT_SWAP_KEY
        There are cases when the hotswap of the changed classes is not needed. E.g. for a tomcat application redeploy there's no need to even try reloading classes and it's only can cause hotswap failure UX issue.

        The flag can be used to skip hotswap after the ProjectTaskManager run session finish. To apply the flag one should add it to ProjectTaskContext user data.

        See Also:
        ProjectTaskContext.withUserData(Key, Object)
